The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of approximating the Dominating Set problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory. The paper uses techniques from communication complexity, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also deals with graph theory, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with approximation algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
